03:17.629 --> 03:19.598
(ROSALEE GRUNTING)

03:25.336 --> 03:27.205
Why you's protecting me?

03:27.272 --> 03:28.640
You can thank your daddy for that.

03:29.582 --> 03:31.645
He's paying as much for you
as all the others combined.

03:33.913 --> 03:35.882
He say that? (GRUNTS)

03:35.949 --> 03:37.249
He my father?

03:38.150 --> 03:39.419
Not in so many words.

03:40.818 --> 03:42.755
But money speaks plenty clear.

03:44.646 --> 03:45.894
His kind.

03:46.824 --> 03:48.961
Sometimes, that's the only way
they know how to talk.

03:52.397 --> 03:53.466
Ben.

03:53.532 --> 03:54.710
Yes, sir?

03:54.967 --> 03:56.502
You keep an eye on her.

04:18.390 --> 04:19.891
JEREMIAH: I had a dog once.

04:19.958 --> 04:21.392
Had that mean look in his eyes,

04:21.459 --> 04:24.216
like any moment he might
rip your throat out.

04:24.830 --> 04:26.811
That girl, she reminds me of him.

04:27.066 --> 04:28.435
You sure your boy can handle that?

04:29.702 --> 04:31.003
You just worry about your men.

04:31.070 --> 04:32.558
Make sure they stay away from her.

04:33.671 --> 04:35.184
I don't need 'em complicating things.

04:36.008 --> 04:37.509
My men, they never see the long game.

04:37.577 --> 04:40.213
Only care about what
satisfies them right now.

04:40.613 --> 04:42.755
Patty could use more men like you.

04:43.282 --> 04:45.383
I said I'd help you capture
the other two, and I will.

04:45.450 --> 04:47.285
Then me and my boy are going home.

04:47.352 --> 04:48.454
(METAL CLATTERING)

04:58.465 --> 05:00.393
He's of a solemn nature, ain't he?

05:01.234 --> 05:02.402
I thought he'd be more excited

05:02.467 --> 05:04.569
to find out he's gonna be rich, but...

05:04.637 --> 05:06.673
I guess he takes after his father.

05:10.008 --> 05:11.677
Them two others,
they're coming for that girl.

05:12.878 --> 05:14.123
You make sure you're ready.

05:17.482 --> 05:19.618
(MEN GRUNTING)

05:21.686 --> 05:24.157
I told you to take out
the shotgun driver first!

05:28.126 --> 05:29.794
(GRUNTS)

05:29.861 --> 05:31.196
Might be I ain't heard you

05:31.263 --> 05:32.764
from all the way up in that tree!

05:32.832 --> 05:34.099
I know I should've gone first.

05:34.166 --> 05:36.102
We got the damn thing.
What you complaining about?

05:36.169 --> 05:37.570
- Damn thing is broken!
- (RATTLES)

05:37.637 --> 05:38.738
Lucky for us, we got ourselves

05:38.804 --> 05:40.605
a honest-to-goodness blacksmith.

05:40.673 --> 05:42.876
Well, we gonna need more than that.

05:42.941 --> 05:45.243
We outnumbered and we outgunned.

05:45.311 --> 05:47.546
(BANGING ON DOOR CONTINUES)

05:47.613 --> 05:50.116
Gonna need a hell of a distraction
to get Rose back.

05:55.554 --> 05:57.122
(SIGHS)

05:57.188 --> 05:58.724
Oh... (SIGHS)

05:58.791 --> 06:01.594
...you know what we could do
with money like this?

06:01.661 --> 06:02.962
Be free and rich.

06:03.029 --> 06:04.830
And live better than them white folks.

06:04.897 --> 06:06.731
Quit your daydreaming and see
if there's some rope in there.

06:06.799 --> 06:08.851
Watch the way you order me around.

06:09.402 --> 06:10.503
I ain't Henry.

06:11.837 --> 06:13.372
Though maybe I am,

06:13.438 --> 06:16.174
seeing as how I'm following
one of your fool-hearted plans

06:16.241 --> 06:17.509
to my death, too.

06:18.176 --> 06:19.244
(GRUNTS)

06:21.481 --> 06:24.217
Goddamn it! The longer
we stand out here fighting,

06:24.282 --> 06:26.117
the less chance we got
of getting Rosalee back.

06:26.185 --> 06:27.253
Who knows what they doing to her?

06:27.318 --> 06:28.720
Ain't nobody care about that house girl.

06:28.787 --> 06:30.555
The only reason I'm helping

06:30.623 --> 06:32.926
is because she knows where the station
is on the other side of that river.

06:38.097 --> 06:39.248
No.

06:39.899 --> 06:41.104
I ain't buying it.

06:41.500 --> 06:43.102
Mmm-mmm.

06:43.169 --> 06:45.738
You act like you don't care
about nobody and nothing.

06:46.371 --> 06:47.559
But I seen you.

06:48.039 --> 06:50.176
Seen you with that bonnet of yours.

06:52.277 --> 06:53.645
Yeah.

06:53.712 --> 06:55.847
Oh, I seen the way you just look at it,

06:55.914 --> 06:58.181
way you be folding it all the time.

06:59.118 --> 07:00.953
There's somebody out there
you care about.

07:01.020 --> 07:03.356
Just holding on to the hope
you gonna see 'em again soon.

07:03.421 --> 07:05.825
So you keep playing big all you want,

07:05.890 --> 07:07.559
but I see you.

07:25.510 --> 07:27.412
AUCTIONEER: Not a
field slave in the bunch,

07:27.479 --> 07:28.813
and this delicate gal

07:28.880 --> 07:31.049
stepping onto the block
won't disappoint.

07:31.549 --> 07:32.684
Lot 25.

07:32.751 --> 07:34.485
One female

07:34.553 --> 07:35.755
of good stock,

07:35.821 --> 07:37.789
well within breeding age, but...

07:37.856 --> 07:40.058
I ain't never been touched by no man.

07:40.125 --> 07:42.795
Claim to be verified
by a doctor upon purchase.

07:42.861 --> 07:44.630
Bidding starts at $400.

07:44.696 --> 07:46.899
- Whoa.
- $400. Do I hear $450?

07:49.669 --> 07:51.236
- Sold.
- MAN: $450.

07:51.303 --> 07:53.406
(CROWD MURMURING)

07:53.472 --> 07:54.606
Do I hear $475?

07:54.673 --> 07:55.675
$500.

07:55.741 --> 07:57.242
MAN: $525.

07:58.142 --> 07:59.178
$550.

07:59.244 --> 08:00.511
MAN: $700.

08:00.578 --> 08:02.948
(MURMURING CONTINUES)

08:05.383 --> 08:06.651
Sold.

08:06.719 --> 08:08.120
(APPLAUSE)

08:08.186 --> 08:09.354
MAN: That's ridiculous.

08:09.421 --> 08:12.258
Sold for $700 to Mr....

08:13.491 --> 08:14.826
Hawkings.

08:21.267 --> 08:24.069
ELIZABETH: "Cinderella went
to the hazel tree and said,

08:24.135 --> 08:26.138
"'Shake and quiver, little tree.

08:26.205 --> 08:28.514
"Throw gold and silver down to me.'

08:29.241 --> 08:32.744
"Then the bird threw down
an even more magnificent dress

08:32.811 --> 08:34.494
"than on the preceding day.

08:34.913 --> 08:37.582
"When Cinderella appeared
at the festival in this dress,

08:37.648 --> 08:40.953
"Everyone was astonished by her beauty.

08:43.955 --> 08:46.291
"The prince had waited until she came,

08:46.358 --> 08:48.125
"and immediately took her by the hand

08:48.472 --> 08:50.106
"and danced only with her."

08:50.528 --> 08:52.798
(PERSISTENT KNOCKING)

09:12.685 --> 09:14.854
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

09:29.968 --> 09:31.304
Has John returned?

09:33.906 --> 09:34.974
No.

09:36.609 --> 09:38.243
I just had to see you again.

09:39.378 --> 09:41.379
Kyle. Kyle, wait.

09:41.446 --> 09:42.447
I've already waited enough.

09:42.513 --> 09:43.715
Kyle.

09:43.782 --> 09:46.085
Kyle. Kyle, no. Wait!

09:47.085 --> 09:48.687
No. Kyle, no.

09:49.721 --> 09:50.889
(GRUNTS)

10:08.285 --> 10:09.286
(SOFT GRUNT)

10:11.600 --> 10:13.067
(SIGHS)

10:13.134 --> 10:14.302
Can I have some water?

10:24.913 --> 10:26.749
(SIGHS) Thank you.

10:32.153 --> 10:33.222
What's your name?

10:34.288 --> 10:35.046
Ben.

10:35.758 --> 10:36.693
Rosalee.

10:37.057 --> 10:38.159
I know.

10:39.961 --> 10:41.496
It's on the slave bill.

10:47.735 --> 10:50.622
I hate when my momma...

10:51.375 --> 10:53.409
...look over my shoulder
in the cookhouse.

10:56.010 --> 10:58.779
I like the sound of the leaves whistling
through the trees on the plantation.

10:58.846 --> 11:01.112
It's like hearing a song on a windy day.

11:02.150 --> 11:05.186
I like the smell of these tin
cookies Miss Suzanna used to buy.

11:06.554 --> 11:07.989
But I never did try one.

11:10.559 --> 11:11.759
Yellow my favorite color.

11:12.428 --> 11:14.331
But the real shiny kind,

11:14.397 --> 11:16.631
like on this ribbon
I used to like to wear.

11:17.231 --> 11:18.999
(SCOFFS)

11:19.067 --> 11:21.970
I ain't just a name on a slave bill.

11:23.004 --> 11:25.167
I ain't just a runaway.

11:25.707 --> 11:28.610
And I ain't just $5,000.

11:32.547 --> 11:34.216
JEREMIAH: Brought the lady some clothes.

11:36.418 --> 11:38.187
Those are my pants.

11:38.253 --> 11:40.523
You don't want the lady to catch
her death, now, do you?

11:45.460 --> 11:47.530
I brought something for you, too, kid.

11:50.131 --> 11:51.457
Just finished reading it.

11:51.767 --> 11:52.914
It's a good one.

11:53.201 --> 11:55.671
About a hunter who becomes
obsessed with the hunt.

11:57.404 --> 11:59.908
So much so, he loses everything else.

12:03.946 --> 12:05.380
Thought that might interest you.

12:07.448 --> 12:08.616
(GUN CLICKS)

12:49.725 --> 12:50.960
It's done.

13:00.836 --> 13:02.751
I have to say, Mr. Hawkings,

13:03.438 --> 13:06.541
I appreciate your aggressiveness.

13:06.609 --> 13:07.975
- What's the use of having money...
- (BELLS JINGLING)

13:08.043 --> 13:09.677
...if you can't recklessly spend it?

13:09.745 --> 13:12.114
(CHUCKLES) I hear that.

13:12.181 --> 13:13.715
I'm a gambling man myself.

13:13.782 --> 13:15.150
Cards?

13:15.216 --> 13:17.418
Um, dice, horseshoes...

13:17.485 --> 13:20.021
...anything works, so long
as there's something to lose.

13:21.422 --> 13:23.390
You plan on buying more slaves?

13:23.457 --> 13:24.692
Or is Ella special?

13:27.062 --> 13:28.733
I'm looking to buy and sell.

13:29.096 --> 13:31.499
I've been traveling
to different auctions

13:31.567 --> 13:33.235
to acquire a feel for the business.

13:34.036 --> 13:35.424
Everywhere I go,

13:35.669 --> 13:37.375
one name always comes up.

13:37.873 --> 13:38.928
Bazil Abbot.

13:39.374 --> 13:41.777
Your auctions have
become legend. Now I see why.

13:44.379 --> 13:45.814
(CLICKS TONGUE)

13:47.381 --> 13:49.184
Any advice from an expert?

13:50.251 --> 13:52.215
Any nigger can pick cotton.

13:53.087 --> 13:55.544
You find some that can do
what no others can,

13:56.023 --> 13:57.559
that's how you make real money.

13:58.592 --> 13:59.899
I'll keep that in mind.

14:00.528 --> 14:04.032
And never, ever inflate
their worth to 'em.

14:04.099 --> 14:06.175
That's how they become intractable.

14:06.668 --> 14:09.447
When they think
they're better than slaves.

14:09.871 --> 14:11.327
Well, like this one here.

14:12.005 --> 14:15.043
Ran from me years ago.

14:15.110 --> 14:16.512
But I got him back.

14:17.678 --> 14:18.880
Now I keep him tethered.

14:20.280 --> 14:21.716
I can hear him anywhere in the house.

14:21.783 --> 14:23.918
(CHUCKLES)

14:23.985 --> 14:25.553
He won't get the best of me again.

14:31.259 --> 14:32.293
ELIZABETH: John.

14:35.330 --> 14:37.032
I would like you to meet Boo.

14:49.110 --> 14:51.446
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

14:51.513 --> 14:54.483
CATO: She could be anywhere, and you
don't even know the way in.

14:55.649 --> 14:57.986
Last chance to take the money and run.

15:21.509 --> 15:23.011
Do you want some more water?

15:24.012 --> 15:25.147
(SOFTLY) Hmm-mmm.

15:27.816 --> 15:29.317
You're not gonna read that?

15:30.451 --> 15:31.434
I don't know.

15:32.486 --> 15:33.579
Maybe.

15:34.523 --> 15:36.507
That hunter obsessed with the hunt.

15:37.658 --> 15:39.002
He talking about your father?

15:45.533 --> 15:47.302
I've seen my father every day of my life

15:47.369 --> 15:49.235
and never even really talked to him.

15:49.571 --> 15:50.773
About anything.

15:50.839 --> 15:51.840
Never?

15:52.874 --> 15:54.043
Hmm-mmm.

15:55.411 --> 15:57.112
I don't think it was out of spite.

15:58.080 --> 15:59.982
He just never noticed me.

16:00.716 --> 16:02.317
(SOFTLY) And I...

16:02.383 --> 16:03.819
...think that's worse.

16:08.956 --> 16:11.293
When my pa would leave
to go on the hunt,

16:12.326 --> 16:14.028
I always wanted to go with him.

16:15.330 --> 16:16.394
Now,

16:16.865 --> 16:18.600
I just wish I was back home.

16:20.936 --> 16:23.038
Well, y'all gonna be getting
your wish pretty soon,

16:23.105 --> 16:24.373
now that you got me.

16:27.042 --> 16:28.211
I'm sorry.

16:32.181 --> 16:33.782
But we need the money to save our land.

16:40.687 --> 16:41.689
(SIGHS)

16:47.427 --> 16:49.029
"Call me Ishmael.

16:49.096 --> 16:50.631
"Some years ago...

16:50.698 --> 16:52.835
"Never mind how long precisely...

16:53.402 --> 16:55.843
"Having little or no money in my purse,

16:56.270 --> 16:58.891
"and nothing particular
to interest me on shore,

16:59.673 --> 17:01.442
"I thought I would sail about a little

17:01.510 --> 17:03.946
"and see the watery part of the world.

17:04.012 --> 17:07.782
"It is a way I have
of driving off the spleen."

17:13.921 --> 17:16.022
Think you'll be able to circle
back with the wagon over there?

17:16.090 --> 17:18.627
(SCOFFS) I got the easy part of this
plan. Let's see you get out first.

17:18.694 --> 17:21.364
I'm making it out with Rosalee.

17:22.363 --> 17:24.499
You just make sure
you're there when we do.

17:32.373 --> 17:33.408
You were right.

17:35.577 --> 17:38.480
That bonnet belong to someone
that I cared about.

17:40.314 --> 17:41.549
My daughter.

17:43.886 --> 17:45.053
- You had a daughter?
- Still do.

17:46.353 --> 17:47.655
She out there somewhere.

17:48.724 --> 17:49.891
My wife, too.

17:52.494 --> 17:55.030
They both had a smile
that would stop your heart.

18:01.169 --> 18:03.010
Used to live Louisiana way.

18:03.370 --> 18:06.507
As cotton gave way to sugar
down there, those two were sold.

18:07.876 --> 18:09.922
I ran the night they were taken.

18:10.677 --> 18:13.415
I followed that slaver's wagon for days.

18:15.550 --> 18:17.619
Got dragged back.

18:19.955 --> 18:23.258
But you wrong about me
hoping I see 'em again.

18:26.527 --> 18:27.761
This here

18:27.829 --> 18:29.127
is a reminder

18:29.497 --> 18:31.932
that a heart ain't made
for nothing but pumping blood.

18:32.000 --> 18:34.503
That's the only thing
it needs to survive.

18:37.872 --> 18:38.907
You remember that.

18:40.308 --> 18:42.511
While you go get
yourself killed for that girl.

19:04.032 --> 19:06.368
<i> ♪ I don't want to drown no more ♪</i>

19:06.434 --> 19:08.904
<i> ♪ Sick of the same old people ♪</i>

19:08.969 --> 19:10.871
<i> ♪ Kind that'll sell your soul ♪</i>

19:10.938 --> 19:13.140
<i> ♪ Trade it for a shining stone ♪</i>

19:13.207 --> 19:15.576
<i> ♪ Ain't nothing in this life for free ♪</i>

19:15.643 --> 19:18.078
<i>-  ♪ Running from the greatest evil ♪</i>
- Come and get it.

19:18.146 --> 19:20.014
<i> ♪ It finally dawned on me ♪</i>

19:20.081 --> 19:21.882
<i> ♪ A man's gotta fight temptation ♪</i>

19:21.948 --> 19:23.951
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

19:28.223 --> 19:31.193
Jeremiah, one of them runners
just rode past in a coach.

19:31.258 --> 19:32.704
It's raining money.

19:33.227 --> 19:34.495
That's a distraction.

19:34.562 --> 19:35.764
The other one will be here for the girl.

19:35.830 --> 19:37.298
I ain't one to pass up on money,

19:37.364 --> 19:38.966
especially when it's flying in the wind.

19:46.073 --> 19:48.009
"If man will strike,

19:48.877 --> 19:50.996
"strike through the mask.

19:51.646 --> 19:55.918
"How can the prisoner reach outside..."

20:03.658 --> 20:08.597
<i> ♪ Keep the wolves from the door ♪</i>

