<i> ♪ Won't be long before I cave
in and open up the door ♪</i>

21:17.331 --> 21:18.699
(BIRD WHISTLING)

21:22.302 --> 21:24.115
ELIZABETH: <i>She's one of the Macon seven.</i>

21:24.706 --> 21:26.440
John, you wouldn't believe
what she's been through

21:26.506 --> 21:28.176
to get from the south to here.

21:30.745 --> 21:32.835
Years in this trade have taught me...

21:33.447 --> 21:35.171
...anybody can be bought and sold.

21:35.783 --> 21:37.385
Not just the niggers.

21:37.452 --> 21:38.723
It's just that, uh,

21:39.187 --> 21:40.889
some lives are worth more than others.

21:41.656 --> 21:42.467
White lives.

21:42.823 --> 21:44.091
Not necessarily.

21:44.158 --> 21:47.171
I hold a very high value on black lives.

21:47.628 --> 21:49.139
The sum total of which

21:49.430 --> 21:51.265
made me a very wealthy man.

21:52.734 --> 21:54.262
I can buy anything I want.

21:55.035 --> 21:56.205
Almost anything.

22:00.207 --> 22:01.942
How about a wager?

22:02.010 --> 22:03.578
You've been such a gracious host.

22:03.645 --> 22:06.214
Where would my manners be if...

22:06.280 --> 22:08.684
I didn't give you the opportunity
to win her back?

22:10.150 --> 22:11.785
You mean you'd be willing to risk

22:11.852 --> 22:15.422
such an expensive acquisition
on a game of chance?

22:15.489 --> 22:16.957
- It depends.
- On what?

22:17.024 --> 22:18.994
On what you're putting up against her.

22:22.729 --> 22:25.065
She lost both her mother
and her father on the run

22:25.132 --> 22:26.663
from your brother's to here.

22:27.034 --> 22:28.303
But she's strong.

22:28.770 --> 22:30.973
And she's smart, she's so smart.

22:35.743 --> 22:38.879
These last few days with her
have been wonderful.

22:42.883 --> 22:46.187
But now I'm afraid that I'm
about to lose both of you.

22:47.988 --> 22:49.032
Lose me?

22:50.725 --> 22:51.880
I'm right here.

22:52.293 --> 22:55.263
And we'll, we'll figure out
what we're gonna do about Boo.

23:02.904 --> 23:04.272
Kyle...

23:05.841 --> 23:06.956
...found her

23:07.875 --> 23:09.181
...in the hideaway.

23:09.677 --> 23:11.712
What? What do you mean? When?

23:11.779 --> 23:13.141
Two days ago.

23:14.014 --> 23:15.416
He knows we're running a station.

23:15.483 --> 23:16.551
Yes.

23:19.920 --> 23:22.023
He's not gonna tell anyone.

23:22.090 --> 23:23.324
How do you know that?

23:27.160 --> 23:28.227
It all happened so fast

23:28.252 --> 23:29.488
that there... there
was no time to think.

23:29.531 --> 23:31.415
Not about you or myself.

23:31.832 --> 23:34.369
I just knew that I had
to protect that little girl.

23:35.503 --> 23:36.838
And Kyle...

23:39.373 --> 23:41.942
He's never stopped loving me.

23:43.311 --> 23:45.414
Even after I broke our engagement.

23:46.548 --> 23:47.749
What did you do?

23:52.218 --> 23:54.718
He said that he would
protect our secret...

23:56.357 --> 23:57.559
- If...
- If you what?

23:59.060 --> 24:00.529
(STAMMERS) If I...

24:08.735 --> 24:10.004
(VOICE BREAKING) How could you?

24:11.872 --> 24:13.207
(GRUNTS)

24:18.012 --> 24:19.548
He came back today.

24:22.816 --> 24:25.018
John, please listen to me. (GASPS)

24:25.085 --> 24:26.320
I've heard enough, Elizabeth!

24:27.221 --> 24:28.423
(GASPING)

24:30.925 --> 24:32.394
(CLATTERING)

24:47.975 --> 24:49.910
(GRUNTING)

25:44.084 --> 25:46.154
So long as you have that knife out,

25:46.719 --> 25:48.422
you may as well give me a hand.

25:51.959 --> 25:54.027
"Sometimes I think there's

25:54.094 --> 25:57.065
"naught... beyond,

25:58.298 --> 26:00.634
"but 'tis enough."

26:25.625 --> 26:26.993
ROSALEE: What's wrong?

26:27.060 --> 26:28.595
He lied to me.

26:34.133 --> 26:35.935
Don't need you anymore.

26:38.972 --> 26:41.341
(BREATHING HEAVILY) God help me.

26:43.876 --> 26:46.079
- ERNESTINE: <i> ♪ There's a church ♪</i>
- ROSALEE: No.

26:46.146 --> 26:48.614
<i> ♪ In the valley ♪</i>

26:48.681 --> 26:52.819
<i> ♪ By the wildwood ♪</i>

26:53.953 --> 26:56.690
<i> ♪ Sweet little church ♪</i>

26:56.757 --> 27:00.594
<i> ♪ On the vale ♪</i>

27:00.661 --> 27:01.962
You ain't here.

27:02.028 --> 27:03.797
In the slaughterhouse...

27:04.898 --> 27:06.401
...or in your head?

27:11.404 --> 27:12.839
Devil's snare.

27:12.905 --> 27:16.877
She was picking it
when you tried to trick her.

27:16.943 --> 27:19.113
I saw some devil's snare
a little while back.

27:19.180 --> 27:20.782
It gonna help with the swelling.

27:22.716 --> 27:24.152
(SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE)

27:25.652 --> 27:27.121
She put it in the dress.

27:30.023 --> 27:31.993
Turns out she think good on her feet.

27:33.192 --> 27:34.662
She gets that from me.

27:36.795 --> 27:38.731
I thought she was soft...

27:40.167 --> 27:41.369
...like Ben.

27:43.670 --> 27:45.672
It's that devil's snare.

27:45.738 --> 27:47.642
I dropped it in the fire.

27:47.708 --> 27:49.743
It's making you crazy.

27:49.809 --> 27:51.211
(SOFTLY) Little Ben.

27:53.113 --> 27:54.315
Ben.

28:00.254 --> 28:02.256
(GASPING)

28:03.623 --> 28:04.959
Run.

28:14.934 --> 28:17.304
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

28:27.480 --> 28:28.781
What's wrong?

28:28.848 --> 28:30.249
I ain't thinking straight.

28:30.316 --> 28:32.752
No, you ain't.

28:32.818 --> 28:35.255
Not since you brought
that boy along with you.

28:35.322 --> 28:38.058
He gonna change the way
you make some choices.

28:38.124 --> 28:39.492
Ain't nothing gonna change.

28:39.559 --> 28:41.928
Children pick up their behavior
from their parents.

28:44.797 --> 28:47.000
He don't look at you
the same way no more.

28:51.671 --> 28:53.473
Blood stains

28:53.540 --> 28:55.642
everything.

28:55.709 --> 28:57.577
Can't get it out for nothing.

28:57.644 --> 28:59.980
You can scrub and scrub.

29:02.149 --> 29:03.918
(CHUCKLES)

29:03.985 --> 29:05.920
Trick's in the lemon water.

29:05.986 --> 29:08.122
Taught my daughter that.

29:09.189 --> 29:10.758
What have you taught your son?

29:12.759 --> 29:14.060
He's fine.

29:15.629 --> 29:18.232
We're going home when the hunt is done.

29:18.298 --> 29:20.801
The hunt ain't never over.

29:21.535 --> 29:22.570
Not for you.

29:23.504 --> 29:24.939
The wolf...

29:25.006 --> 29:27.608
...doesn't always know he's a wolf.

29:27.673 --> 29:29.509
But he suspects.

29:31.112 --> 29:32.380
(EXHALES)

29:33.313 --> 29:35.650
(MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

30:20.707 --> 30:22.440
TOM: Four fingers, two cubes.

30:23.210 --> 30:24.546
You remember, don't you?

30:25.646 --> 30:26.681
Yes, <i> massa.</i>

30:26.746 --> 30:28.015
Well, get to it.

30:39.027 --> 30:40.328
No.

30:40.394 --> 30:41.663
Don't be scared, Rose.

30:41.730 --> 30:43.298
You're safe now. You're home.

30:46.768 --> 30:48.502
I was never safe here.

30:49.737 --> 30:50.971
(SIGHS)

30:54.442 --> 30:57.212
You... let him...

30:58.279 --> 31:00.048
...do this to me.

31:01.515 --> 31:02.949
You let him

31:03.017 --> 31:05.353
do it over and over,

31:05.419 --> 31:07.487
till my arms were tore up.

31:07.554 --> 31:08.889
(SHAKILY) I'm your daughter.

31:09.991 --> 31:11.959
And you just sat there,

31:12.025 --> 31:14.428
reading the newspaper,
like it was any other day.

31:17.231 --> 31:19.200
I'm not gonna let you ignore me no more.

31:19.267 --> 31:21.068
You ungrateful little house bitch.

31:21.135 --> 31:22.904
After all your mother has done
to get you out of those fields.

31:22.970 --> 31:24.072
I should have you whipped again.

31:24.137 --> 31:25.807
Be my pleasure, boss.

31:27.707 --> 31:29.476
AUGUST: These two,
they're the last ones.

31:30.944 --> 31:32.246
I ain't lyin'.

31:35.183 --> 31:37.352
Charlotte's home. I'm done with this.

31:38.485 --> 31:41.387
Some animals ain't meant to be tamed.

31:41.454 --> 31:43.124
It's in their bones,

31:43.191 --> 31:46.461
to scream and run wild.

31:47.762 --> 31:49.496
Primal nature...

31:50.999 --> 31:52.967
...and a hunger for blood.

31:53.600 --> 31:55.035
For flesh.

31:59.439 --> 32:01.041
(SCREAMING)

32:02.676 --> 32:04.145
Every time you look at these,

32:04.212 --> 32:06.046
you're going to remember me.

32:06.112 --> 32:07.747
For the rest of your life.

32:07.814 --> 32:09.182
If it wasn't for me,

32:09.250 --> 32:11.719
you'd still be messin'
with your <i> massa</i> flowers

32:11.784 --> 32:12.986
outside the big house.

32:13.053 --> 32:14.588
I didn't mean to hurt him.

32:14.655 --> 32:15.924
We all know you didn't.

32:17.157 --> 32:18.827
I meant to kill him.

32:18.893 --> 32:21.296
It was the first free thing I ever done.

32:21.361 --> 32:23.764
And it ain't gonna be my last.

32:27.435 --> 32:29.369
That's why we do everything.

32:29.435 --> 32:31.938
To make anew.

32:32.005 --> 32:34.575
To leave a little bit of us behind...

32:36.077 --> 32:37.878
...while we fade to dust.

32:40.281 --> 32:43.585
And we all fade to dust.

32:49.456 --> 32:50.491
(GRUNTS)

32:50.558 --> 32:51.559
(GUN COCKS)

33:03.204 --> 33:04.739
Yah, yah! Yah!

33:05.639 --> 33:08.443
(BOTH GRUNTING)

33:16.818 --> 33:17.952
- You are my daughter...
- (SCREAMS)

33:18.019 --> 33:20.354
...and there is no freedom for you.

33:20.421 --> 33:22.557
(GRUNTING)

33:24.090 --> 33:25.159
(GROANS)

33:27.694 --> 33:28.929
(GRUNTS)

33:36.436 --> 33:37.604
(GUN COCKING)

33:40.541 --> 33:41.742
(GROANS)

33:44.678 --> 33:45.713
(SOBS)

33:45.779 --> 33:47.415
(GROWLS)

33:48.715 --> 33:49.850
Aah!

33:52.386 --> 33:54.289
(WAILING)

33:55.556 --> 33:58.159
(ROSALEE WAILING, SOBBING)

34:01.262 --> 34:03.296
TOM: You learned how to look
the other way from me.

34:03.363 --> 34:05.698
You kept your head down
your whole life in my house.

34:05.765 --> 34:07.568
And it was easier, wasn't it?

34:07.635 --> 34:09.569
Without the fighting. The starving.

34:09.635 --> 34:11.304
Being under constant assault.

34:11.370 --> 34:13.739
That boy won't stay fooled for long.

34:13.806 --> 34:16.275
You ain't made for runnin'.

34:16.342 --> 34:17.512
No!

34:17.579 --> 34:18.879
You're coming home!

34:18.946 --> 34:20.714
(SOBBING) I'd rather die than be here!

34:20.781 --> 34:22.850
I own you!

34:24.184 --> 34:26.052
(WAILS)

34:26.120 --> 34:27.422
(GASPS)

34:30.623 --> 34:31.759
Oh...

34:32.993 --> 34:34.262
(GASPS)

34:37.063 --> 34:38.366
BEN: Pa...

34:39.466 --> 34:40.734
Pa...

34:41.900 --> 34:43.503
(PANTING)

34:43.571 --> 34:45.072
It hurts, Pa.

34:45.705 --> 34:47.373
(BEN GROANS)

34:52.911 --> 34:54.581
BEN: Pa...

34:54.649 --> 34:56.284
(MUMBLES)

34:58.887 --> 35:00.488
(GROANING)

35:00.555 --> 35:01.723
Pa.

35:05.426 --> 35:06.928
Pa.

35:10.664 --> 35:12.966
It's all right.

35:13.033 --> 35:14.568
It's all right, I got you.

35:26.961 --> 35:27.962
NOAH: Rose!

35:37.571 --> 35:38.772
Where Cato?

35:38.839 --> 35:40.408
He was supposed to be here!

35:47.446 --> 35:48.749
JEREMIAH: Go!

35:48.816 --> 35:50.116
- (SHOUTING)
- NOAH: He left us.

35:50.183 --> 35:51.451
We gotta move.

35:52.518 --> 35:53.800
There he is!

35:54.488 --> 35:56.156
JEREMIAH: Hold it right there!

35:56.223 --> 35:57.457
Whoa!

35:57.524 --> 35:59.426
- (SNORTING)
- (SHOUTING)

35:59.493 --> 36:00.862
What you waitin' on? Get in!

36:02.261 --> 36:03.529
Hyah, hyah!

36:03.596 --> 36:04.765
(SHOUTING)

36:04.830 --> 36:05.832
(GUNSHOT)

36:05.899 --> 36:07.734
- The horses, boys.
- Oh!

36:15.776 --> 36:17.911
Whoa. Road's blocked.

36:17.977 --> 36:19.613
Got to go the rest of the way on foot.

36:21.415 --> 36:23.383
Here.

36:23.450 --> 36:24.685
Where we goin', house girl?

36:24.752 --> 36:27.121
That undertaker say
we go west, look for a bridge

36:27.187 --> 36:28.521
look like a crooked smile.

36:28.587 --> 36:29.790
I hear water that way.

36:29.857 --> 36:31.025
Come on.

36:32.625 --> 36:34.095
(PANTING)

36:35.694 --> 36:36.763
Ah!

36:36.830 --> 36:37.832
(SCREAMS)

36:39.966 --> 36:41.434
We gotta cut it down from there.

36:41.502 --> 36:43.638
- Where's your knife?
- Ah! Must've fell.

36:43.703 --> 36:45.038
(HORSE NEIGHS)

36:48.274 --> 36:49.576
(GRUNTS)

36:49.642 --> 36:51.511
(GUNSHOT)

36:51.578 --> 36:53.113
Don't hit the girl! We need her alive!

36:53.180 --> 36:54.381
Aah!

36:54.448 --> 36:56.083
(GUNSHOTS)

36:56.149 --> 36:57.617
Where the arrows coming from?

36:57.685 --> 36:58.786
There.

36:58.852 --> 37:00.720
- (GUNSHOT)
- We gotta get to that bridge.

37:00.787 --> 37:03.191
We gotta cross and cut it down
before they can follow us.

37:04.825 --> 37:06.993
I got him. Go. Find it.

37:07.060 --> 37:09.029
And here. Here. Hold on.

37:13.933 --> 37:15.035
Hurry up!

37:17.671 --> 37:19.073
(GRUNTS)

37:21.475 --> 37:22.743
We gotta move.

37:23.611 --> 37:24.612
(GROANS)

37:28.448 --> 37:30.050
Ah...

37:32.787 --> 37:35.890
(GRUNTS, GROANS)

37:35.957 --> 37:38.125
(GUNSHOTS CONTINUE)

38:12.258 --> 38:13.593
I found the bridge.

38:14.428 --> 38:15.796
Where Cato?

38:18.364 --> 38:20.033
(GUNSHOT)

38:29.977 --> 38:31.745
What do you want me to say?

38:31.812 --> 38:32.946
I did it for you!

38:33.013 --> 38:34.547
Oh, don't you put this on me!

38:34.613 --> 38:36.449
You went to bed with him
while you were engaged.

38:36.517 --> 38:38.352
And then again, with me,
before we were married.

38:41.955 --> 38:43.457
What are you saying?

38:44.258 --> 38:45.759
Tell me.

38:45.825 --> 38:48.201
What happened? Tell me
everything that happened.

38:48.562 --> 38:50.113
You weren't here.

38:50.698 --> 38:53.409
I was alone and scared.

38:54.067 --> 38:55.769
You started us down this path.

38:55.836 --> 38:58.571
You brought this danger into our home.

39:02.442 --> 39:03.944
You ever played "puff and dart?"

39:04.011 --> 39:05.379
No.

39:05.446 --> 39:07.348
But I have to warn you, I pick
up on things pretty quickly.

39:07.413 --> 39:08.515
(CHUCKLES)

39:08.582 --> 39:09.950
Well, then, best three out of five.

39:10.017 --> 39:12.785
I don't want anyone accusing
me of swindling you.

39:12.852 --> 39:14.020
Fine.

39:15.055 --> 39:16.256
- Aah!
- (SCREAMS)

39:16.323 --> 39:17.324
(GROANS)

39:17.390 --> 39:18.591
You think me a fool?

39:18.658 --> 39:20.894
I know you're Tom Macon's
abolitionist brother.

39:22.495 --> 39:24.230
(GRUNTING)

39:25.598 --> 39:27.801
The value of your life, Mr. Hawkes,

39:27.868 --> 39:30.537
has just plummeted to zero.

39:30.604 --> 39:34.341
How dare you blame me
for the way that I saved us?

39:34.408 --> 39:37.076
"Us," Elizabeth? Did you do this for us?

39:37.142 --> 39:38.812
Or did you do it for that little girl?

39:43.116 --> 39:44.985
- What are we supposed to do now?
- I don't know.

39:45.051 --> 39:46.553
Tell me what I'm supposed to do now!

39:46.620 --> 39:47.888
I don't know!

39:47.953 --> 39:49.355
JOHN: I'll tell you what I want to do.

39:49.422 --> 39:51.290
I want to slap you
for letting him touch you.

39:51.357 --> 39:52.560
(GRUNTING)

39:55.294 --> 39:57.731
And I want to kill him for
even thinking that he could.

39:58.631 --> 39:59.799
(GRUNTS)

40:00.966 --> 40:02.403
You know what I did down south?

40:03.370 --> 40:04.638
(GROANING)

40:04.705 --> 40:06.172
(GUN COCKS)

40:06.238 --> 40:08.641
I almost beat a man to death, Elizabeth.

40:08.709 --> 40:11.812
Go. It'll look like a slave got
loose and killed his <i> massa.</i>

40:13.346 --> 40:16.316
And then I left him there
for Clyde to kill.

40:16.383 --> 40:17.584
I'm a man of the law

40:17.651 --> 40:19.053
and I feel completely lawless!

40:25.292 --> 40:27.294
(SOFTLY) Okay, it's okay.

40:28.528 --> 40:30.765
BOO: The bad man was gonna hurt you.

40:30.830 --> 40:31.832
It's okay.

40:32.631 --> 40:34.067
He's not a bad man.

40:36.303 --> 40:37.705
(RAPID KNOCKING AT DOOR)

40:47.580 --> 40:49.783
A friend of a friend sent us.

40:49.850 --> 40:50.851
(PANTING)

40:52.986 --> 40:54.354
Rosalee!

40:55.022 --> 40:56.424
(GASPS)

40:57.357 --> 40:59.125
(SOBBING)

